-- Turkey Stocks: Akenerji, Aksa Enerji, Hurriyet Gazeticilik Move
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-04-02T15:28:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-02/turkey-stocks-akenerji-aksa-enerji-hurriyet-gazeticilik-move.html
Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  added 0.9 percent to 62,969.32 at the close in Istanbul.  The following stocks were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Akenerji Elektrik Uretim AS (AKENR)  , a producer and
distributor of electricity and steam, fell 0.9 percent to 2.14
liras. Turkey over the weekend increased natural gas prices by
as much as 18.7 percent and electricity prices by 8.1 percent.
The index tracking Turkish electicity producers fell 0.8 percent
today.  Aksa Enerji Uretim AS (AKSEN)  , a utility, fell 1.8
percent to 3.92 liras.  Hurriyet Gazetecilik AS (HURGZ)  , the publisher of
Hurriyet newspaper, dropped 1.7 percent to 1.16 liras after
reporting a loss last year of 235.7 million liras ($132
million), almost quadruple analysts’ estimates.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
 bharvey11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
